<Review ID>9902323
<Product Name>Philips HDD1630 6 GB MP3 Player
<Title>Had to send for repairs twice
<Date>Sat Mar 03 00:00:00 CST 2007
<Content>This player has a problem that requires it to be sent for service to the repair center.  Occasionally, on a power down, and then the subsequent power on, the Philips GOGEAR will become frozen with the advise to plug your GOGEAR to your PC.  And when you attach the GOGEAR to the PC the Device Manager will not recognize the MP3 player.  Therefore you cannot repair the GOGEAR.  A soft reset will not work (power button and volume + button at same time).  You call customer service and they are helpful, but the only thing that you can do in this situation is send the GOGEAR to the repair center.  This is the second time this has happened to me.  Once with the PHILIPS 6 GB HDD1630/17 and now the second time with the replacement model they sent me HDD1635/17.  The only reason I give this item 2 stars is because when it works it is great.  And the customer service representative is helpful.  But that being said it is frustrating having to repair the items.  I was under warrenty and have not had to pay anything outside  the shipping and handling to get the GOGEAR to the repair center.  But I am not sure I would pay anymore money on an item that is cronically breaking.  
<Overall>2

<Review ID>9847172
<Product Name>Philips HDD1630 6 GB MP3 Player
<Title>Love it when it works (aka MOST of the time)
<Date>Thu Mar 08 00:00:00 CST 2007
<Content>I've had my Go Gear for over a year and most of the time its wonderful. The battery lasts me all day, sound is great, no problem with navigation. Then there are the times when it acts up...For some reason, and I can't identify any cause, there are times when the battery doesn't charge fully and when navigating back to the main menu doesn't work smoothly.  There have been a few times when the player has frozen up, but these are pretty rare and were resolved with the soft reset (pwr + up vol). The rubber cover that comes with the player is all but useless, so I wish I had purchased the control case from the start so my player wouldn't have the few scratches it has on the front. With the control case, the player is fully protected and can be hung on a belt loop or pack. Over all, I really like this player. It has been a great alternative to the iPOD empire and I would buy Philips again.  
<Overall>4

